description: A large woman in a red dress is on a landline phone indoors, looking out a window. Outside, a man in a brown coat and hat stands pointing up at a striped cat perched high in a tree. The woman is calling her neighbor, Sylvia, to inform her that Sylvia's husband, Henry, has chased her cat up the tree yet again. The absurdity lies in a grown man being the one repeatedly terrifying a cat into seeking refuge in a tree, reversing the typical dynamic. This unusual behavior by Henry is the central humorous element.
caption: “Sorry to bother you, Sylvia, but your Henry's over here and he's got my cat treed again.”
